Wash and dry all produce. Preheat #oven{} or #toaster oven{} to 400 degrees. Thinly slice @dried chorizo{2%oz} into rounds. Cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{16%oz} into ½-inch cubes. Halve, peel, and finely dice @red onion{1}. Halve and pit @avocado{1}. Scoop out flesh with a #spoon{}, then thinly slice.

> Wakey, wakey, it's eggs and ... chorizo? Yep, we're spicing up breakfast time with Spain's most famous sausage. It adds paprika-laced flavor to this eggy sandwich, as well as to the crispy, skillet-fried potato hash that's on the side. A few slices of avocado on top are the finishing touch that makes this a perfect meal for powering through your day.

Add chorizo to a large pan over medium heat. Cook, tossing occasionally, until oil has rendered and rounds are crispy, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove from pan with #slotted spoon{} and set aside, keeping as much oil in pan as possible.

Increase heat under pan to medium high. Add potatoes and cook, tossing, until crisped, ~{15-20%minutes}. Add onion and cook until softened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove mixture from pan and set aside. Cover with #foil{} to keep warm.

Split @brioche buns{2} in half and place on a #baking sheet{} cut-side up. Place a handful of @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} on each of the bun tops. Toast in oven until cheese is melted and buns are golden brown, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Carefully wipe out pan with a #paper towel{}, then heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in it over medium-high heat. Crack @eggs{2} into a #small bowl{}, checking for any bits of shell. Gently slide into pan. Cook eggs sunny-side up to desired doneness, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Layer chorizo and avocado slices inside buns, then top each with an egg to make sandwiches. Serve with hash and any remaining chorizo or avocado on the side.